**Key takeaways:**
- Risk-off open: VIX +6.24% to 18.05, oil +3% on disputed Iran/Hormuz warship strike report, dollar bid, gold paradoxically off 1.57% (supply-shock + dollar-haven combo, not systemic risk)
- Light macro calendar (Factory Orders 10:00, Williams 12:50, Senior Loan Officer Survey 14:03) — tape will be driven by Hormuz headlines and the **PLTR + BWXT** earnings prints
- Defense complex deeply oversold: NOC RSI 21, LMT 23, SYK 21, LHX 29, RTX 31 — positioning unwind, no near-term catalyst
- Heavy week ahead: ANET/CCJ/LDOS/LEU 5/5, FTNT 5/6, RKLB/VST/MP 5/7
- Watchlist movers: **OUST +7.83%** (clean 200-SMA breakout), **BAH +3.18%** (recovery bounce, still below 200-SMA), **MP +2.28%** (T1 breakout)

**Data quality flags surfaced in the brief:**
- Bitcoin Schwab feed showing $34.89 — clearly a proxy/ETF mislabel; news confirms spot BTC reclaimed $80K
- PWR $752 (z 3.5) and SYK $296 (z -4.0) anomalies confirmed as real price levels, not bad ticks
- FRED timeout (non-critical, 2Y carried as prev close)
